Description: The main package loading KBI from files.
There are files whose lines are broken. The data is split on two rows, despite the fact that it should be on one row. For the puposes of these files, there is a program created which is called linestiker and is located under SCRIPT_DIR= /export/home/oracle/admin/odi_datastage/scripts on DEV and /u04/odi/scripts on PROD. The name of the files whose rows are split are enumerated with ; in the evaluate expression of the check_source_name variable (ex. dwilogx).
Parameters: #GLOBAL.g_var_target_owner - The schema of the target table #GLOBAL.g_var_target_name - The name of the target table #GLOBAL.g_var_source_name - The name of the source table (<schema>.<table>) #GLOBAL.g_var_scenario_name - The name of the scenario of a mapping to execute #GLOBAL.g_var_db_link_from_trg_to_me - Database link created in the target schema RIA_IFACE pointing to the source RIA_TRANSIT_TEST. The physical schema RIA_TRANSIT_TEST is located the topology under the Oracle technology, under the dwhdev/dwhprod Data Server. The Database link is set in the "Instance / dblink (Data Server)" property of the dwhdev/dwhprod Data Server. #GLOBAL.g_var_eff_date - Date for loading. Mask: YYYY-MM-DD
Change History: Created: 2017-09-28 by Koko
